input: Create a simple website homepage with basic navigation and contact form

steps:
Uses: Input 1 (Website Content), Input 2 (Website Structure)
Action: Create HTML page structure with placeholder elements matching content requirements
Produces: Base HTML template
Stores/Sends To: Local file system (index.html)

Uses: Input 2 (Website Structure), Input 6 (Navigation Structure)
Action: Generate responsive navigation menu using derived navigation structure
Produces: Navigation component HTML/CSS
Stores/Sends To: index.html header section

Uses: Input 3 (Contact Form Fields), Input 7 (Contact Form HTML)
Action: Implement contact form with specified fields and validation
Produces: Form component HTML
Stores/Sends To: index.html contact section

Uses: Input 4 (Styling Preferences), Input 8 (CSS Stylesheet)
Action: Generate CSS stylesheet implementing visual preferences
Produces: Main stylesheet
Stores/Sends To: /css/main.css

Uses: Input 1 (Website Content), Inputs 6-8 (Derived assets)
Action: Combine all assets into deployable package
Produces: Website Files Archive
Stores/Sends To: /dist/website.zip

Uses: Input 5 (Hosting Credentials), Input 10 (Hosting API Endpoint), Input 9 (Website Archive)
Action: Deploy website via hosting platform API with authentication
Produces: Deployment response
Stores/Sends To: Hosting platform server

Uses: Input 10 (Hosting API Endpoint), Step 6 output
Action: Verify deployment status and retrieve live URL
Produces: Deployment confirmation report
Stores/Sends To: User console output

Inputs:
1. Website Content
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: User
   Input Data: Text content, images, and media assets for homepage
   Bound Reference: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

2. Website Structure
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: User
   Input Data: Page hierarchy and navigation relationships (e.g., "Home > About > Contact")
   Bound Reference: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

3. Contact Form Fields
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: User
   Input Data: List of required form fields with validation rules (e.g., "Name [required], Email [required, email format]")
   Bound Reference: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

4. Styling Preferences
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: User
   Input Data: Color scheme, font choices, layout preferences
   Bound Reference: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

5. Hosting Platform Credentials
   Source Type: USER-CONTROLLED
   Source Origin: User
   Input Data: API keys, username/password, or deployment credentials for hosting service
   Bound Reference: Requires explicit user provision or linkage.

6. Navigation Structure
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Derived from Website Structure
   Input Data: Structured navigation menu data (e.g., JSON/XML format)
   Bound Reference: Input 2 (Website Structure)
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

7. Contact Form HTML
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Generated from Contact Form Fields
   Input Data: HTML markup with form validation attributes
   Bound Reference: Input 3 (Contact Form Fields)
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

8. CSS Stylesheet
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Generated from Styling Preferences
   Input Data: Compiled CSS file implementing visual preferences
   Bound Reference: Input 4 (Styling Preferences)
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

9. Website Files Archive
   Source Type: DERIVABLE
   Source Origin: Combined website assets
   Input Data: Zipped directory containing HTML, CSS, JS, and media files
   Bound Reference: Inputs 1,6,7,8
   Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

10. Hosting Platform API Endpoint
    Source Type: SYSTEM-RETRIEVABLE
    Source Origin: Hosting provider's API documentation
    Input Data: REST API endpoint URL for deployment (e.g., "https://api.hosting.com/v1/deploy")
    Bound Reference: Input 5 (Hosting Platform Credentials)
    Note: [DEPTH STOP - Terminal input, do not further decompose]

Outputs:
1. Website File Structure
   Type: File system directory
   Description: Organized HTML, CSS, JS, and media files
   Location: Local development environment

2. Deployed Website
   Type: Live web presence
   Description: Publicly accessible website at specified domain
   Location: Hosting platform server

3. Deployment Confirmation
   Type: Text report
   Description: Deployment status, URL, and error messages if applicable
   Location: User console/output
